of American poetry in France, and the place of feminism in contemporary French writing. Each interview is accompanied by samples of the writer's work in French and in Gavronsky's English translations.Toward a New Poetics provides a highly informative cultural and critical perspective on contemporary writing in France, introducing us to works which are now transforming the idea of literature itself.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Frenchy20th centuryvInterviews. 0aFrench literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aLiteraturexPhilosophy. 0aPoetics. 4aGeneral. 4aPoetry. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh1 aGavronsky, Serge, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008793440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091523740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520915237423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520915237/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles